deck: Darna returns for the 90's in a new film that will be followed by another and a TV series later.
name: Darna ang Pagbabalik!

deck: The Superheroine with the most films to her credit returns again.
name: Bira! Darna Bira!

deck: Darna at ang Babaing Lawin (Darna and the Hawkwoman)
name: Darna at ang Babaing Lawin

deck: Directed by Peter Jackson, this is the second remake of classic movie about the giant ape of the horrifying Skull Island and the actress who needed care. A truly strong and inspiring tale of beauty and the beast.
description: A desperate movie producer tricks his cast and crew into travelling to a mysterious island in a last ditch effort to save his reputation and his finances. Once there, the group encounters dangers they could have never imagined and the starlet actress, Ann Darrow, is kidnapped by the most feared monster on the terrifying island. Now, everyone must band together to trek through the foreign and deadly terrain to try and save Anne and get back to the ship before they are all killed.
name: King Kong

deck: A giant ape is captured and brought to New York
name: King Kong

deck: King Kong battles a robot of himself. This film marks the first appearance of Gorosaurus
name: King Kong Escapes

deck: Third installment in The Crow film series
name: The Crow Salvation

deck: The children of Captain America, Black Widow, Ant-Man, The Wasp, Thor, Black Panther, and Hawkeye join forces with Iron Man and Hulk against Ultron and his robotic forces.
description:
Special Features

All of the following special features are included on the DVD and Blu-ray releases:

  • Legacy: The Making of Next Avengers: Heroes of Tomorrow - Featurette
  • Kid Power: Next-Gen Marvel - Featurette
  • A First Look at Hulk vs. Wolverine
  • A First Look at Hulk vs. Thor
name: Next Avengers Heroes of Tomorrow

deck: How does it feel to have the G.I. Joes pop out of comics and straight into a superb action flick? Well, read on...
description:
The opening scene starts in the year 1641. A man is brought to judgement for his acts of treason. He tells the king that though he may not live, his sons will carry the fight on. The king does not pay heed to him and has his face clamped in a red-hot iron mask.

Present day.
A team of NATO soldiers are being given a demo of M.A.R.S. nanite missiles. The NATO prepares for departure with the missile. Midway, they are attack by a COBRA
name: G.I. Joe The Rise of Cobra

deck: An interstellar teleportation device, found in Egypt, leads to a planet with humans resembling ancient Egyptians who worship the god Ra.
name: Stargate

deck: A little known film based on a little known comic character. Fitting.
description: Reporter Jane Arden is convinced that debutante Martha Blanton has a story to tell, and her instinct is proven correct when Martha is killed. Jane is also sure that the man the police arrest is not the man who killed Martha. Ed Towers, the newspaper's editor, fires Jane for incompetence and then meets secretly with her. He hands her an undercover assignment, introducing her to Bill Clifton, a special investigator for the Jewelers Association. Bill explains that Martha was involved in a jewel smuggling ring and was killed when she tried to leave. They suspect the reputable firm of Thayer and Co. of being the ringleader, but have been unable to find any proof of wrongdoing. Jane's first act is to try and sell Thayer and Co. some stolen jewels, using a false name, just as Albert Thayer and Dr. George Vanders are looking for another woman to take Martha's place in the gang. Vanders is impressed by Jane, but Thayer is suspicious. Jane agrees to smuggle in some jewels from Bermuda, but on board the ship, Thayer sees Ed leaving Jane's cabin and has him followed. Learning that he is a newspaperman, Thayer cables Vanders with the news, but Vanders decides to go through with their plans and intends to kill Jane after the jewels are successfully brought into the country. Jane meets Vanders and his accomplice, Lola Martin, on the ship but does not realize that they are involved in the gang. Meanwhile, Thayer kidnaps Ed and holds him hostage. In Bermuda, Lola becomes jealous of Vanders' attentions to Jane and refuses to steal the jewels. Vanders walks in on Jane while she is phoning Bill with the latest plans, but he warns her that Ed is in danger if she does anything to jeopardize the robbery. When they arrive at the party, however, they discover that the jewels have already been stolen. Vanders then realizes that Lola committed the robbery in order to have them all for herself. Jane and Vanders wait for Lola in her room, and when she arrives, Lola tells Vanders that his identity is known and suggests that they escape together. Unknown to Vanders, Ed has escaped and tricked Thayer into a confession. He flys to Bermuda, where he sees Vanders and Lola leaving with Jane. He chases them and finally shoots Vanders. On the boat returning home, Ed reveals that he loves Jane and they kiss.
name: The Adventures of Jane Arden

deck: Simon Templer, the Saint, Returns for a modern interpretation
name: The Saint

deck: Simon Templer takes Manhattan, and it almost takes him out of play.
name: The `Saint' in New York

deck: An unsuccessful 1997 TV-pilot, which has never been aired in the US. It has been shown on television in the UK, Germany (2005), Puerto Rico, Brazil, Uruguay, Israel (2001) and Austria.
description: The Justice League of America is up against an evil Weather Man (Miguel Ferrer) , who intents to destroy New Metro City.
name: Justice League of America

deck: The film is a satire of the Catholic Church, written and directed by Kevin Smith, who also co-stars in the film as Silent Bob along with an ensemble cast.
description: The abortion clinic worker Bethany (Linda Fiorentino) is the last descendant of Mary & Joseph, and she has to prevent the two fallen angels Loki (Matt Damon) and Bartleby (Ben Affleck) from destroying existence. On her mission she encounters an angel (Alan Rickman), a muse (Salma Hayek), the 13th apostle (Chris Rock), the prophets Jay & Silent Bob (Jason Mewes & Kevin Smith), some villains from hell (Jason Lee & Ethan Suplee) and finally God herself (Alanis Morissette).
name: Dogma

deck: The Legend of Zorro is a sequel to 1998's The Mask of Zorro, also directed by Martin Campbell, starring Antonio Banderas, Catherine Zeta-Jones and Rufus Sewell.
name: The Legend of Zorro

deck: Disney's animated version of the jungle hero.
description: A man raised by gorillas must choose whether to live as a human or stay among the gorillas, after falling in love with a human woman.
name: Tarzan

deck: Tarzan the Ape Man was the first Tarzan film to star Weissmuller and O'Sullivan, and marked the first appearance of the character of Cheeta the chimpanzee.
description: James Parker, Harry Holt and Jane Parker set off in search of the fabled graveyard of the elephants in deepest Africa, only to encounter a wild man raised by apes.
name: Tarzan the Ape Man

deck: Tarzan and his Mate was the second in the Tarzan film series to star Johnny Weissmuller.
description: Tarzan and Jane living in the Jungle meet up with Henry Holt and Marlin Arlington on their way to take ivory from an elephant burial ground. After Tarzan gets shot Jane is forced to choose between two worlds.
name: Tarzan and his Mate

deck: Tarzan Escapes was the third in the MGM Tarzan series to feature Johnny Weissmuller as Tarzan.
description: Jane's two cousins Eric and Rita arrive in Africa to tell Jane about a fortune left to her back in their world and to try and convince her to return with them.
name: Tarzan Escapes

deck: Human infused with alien DNA is on the search for mate.
name: Species 3

deck: Human infused with alien DNA is on the search for mate.
name: Species: The Awakening

deck: Human infused with alien DNA is on the search for mate.
name: Species

deck: Human infused with alien DNA is on the search for mate.
name: Species 2

deck: This live-action version of the popular Japanese series Dragon Ball.
description: A villainous king known as Emperor Horn has stolen the mystical power of the "Dragon Pearls" in an attempt to possess them all and rule the world! When all but one of the pearls has been stolen, the former rag-tag group of guardian heroes (led by Goku) of the mysterious magic jewels decides to band together and take some big action! Led by a pig-headed wizard and a half-turtle martial arts master, the team first takes on King Horn's army in a desperate bid to stop him from gaining control of the Dragon Pearls.
name: Dragon Ball: The Magic Begins

deck: The final part of the popular series Hana Yori Dango.
description: The final part of the popular series Hana Yori Dango ends with an adventure around the world. Finally, the feuding couple, Tsukushi and Tsukasa are engaged and just when they think everything will be happily ever after, the precious heirloom - a tiara called the Smile of Venus, is stolen. The two go on a search to retrieve the tiara heading off to Las Vegas, Hong Kong and other places, however each time they think they have recovered the tiara, it slips away from them. Can their love hold up to the test?
name: Hana Yori Dango Final

deck: Inu-Yasha has mastered the ultimate attack of the Tetsusaiga and continues his battle for the Shikon Jewel shards with Kagome, Shippo, Sango, and Miroku. Unfortunately, a freak occurance with a jewel shard has brought to life an incarnation of a demonic enemy sealed by Inu-Yasha's father. Inu-Yasha must surpass his father and destroy this demon or every soul in Japan will be consumed.
name: Inuyasha the Movie: Affections Touching Across Time

description: A retelling of Dragon Ball's origins, this is a different version of the meeting of Goku, Bulma, Oolong, and Yamucha. They are all looking for the dragon balls for different reasons when they cross paths with an evil king named Gourmeth, who is also looking for the dragon balls.
name: Dragon Ball Movie 1: Curse of the Blood Rubies

deck: After the events of Aliens. Ellen Ripley, Newt, Hicks, and Bishop are in deep sleep until a fire is detected on the Sulaco. All four of them are ejected to safety and land on Fiorina 'Fury' 161, a foundry facility and penal colony inhabited by all-male inmates with "double-Y" chromosome patterns. Soon she discovers an Alien caused the fire and discovers it's now on the planet.
description: This movie has been adapted into a three issue mini-series.
name: Alien 3

deck: It was the fourth in the MGM Tarzan series to feature Johnny Weissmuller as Tarzan.
description:
After a plane crash, a baby is rescued by Cheeta , Tarzan's chimpanzee.  
 
Tarzan and Jane adopt the child and name him "Boy". Five years later, a search party comes looking for Boy, because he is the heir to a fortune worth millions.
name: Tarzan Finds a Son!

deck: George A. Romero and Stephen King are back to bring us another series of Horror stories.
description:
"Old Chief Wooden Head" features a cigar store Indian as the title character. Decorating the general goods store Ray and Martha Spruce. The elderly couple see their hometown being progressively abandoned, dying. When three thugs arrive to rob them, there is nobody left to help them. They die. But the Chief comes to life to avenge. Demonstrating his skills at scalping thugs.

"The Raft" features Deke, Laverne, Rachel and Randy. All four college students on vacation. They are traveling by car in a fairly isolated spot when they locate a lake. They think it is an ideal place to stop and swim. They make their way by foot to a wooden raft abandoned nearby. Soon they are attacked by a mysterious blob which proceeds to hunt them down and consume them in the course of two days. No remains left behind. Only their abandoned car and a long-forgotten sign pointing "No Swimming".

"The Hitchhiker" features the story of Annie Lansing and an unnamed (male) hitchhiker. Annie is a businesswoman and married to a wealthy attorney. She also has a lover who she chooses to meet several miles away from her home. After a sexual encounter, Annie decides to drive back home at some speed. (Intending to arrive before her husband and greet him there). Annie causes a hit-and-run accident, killing the hitchhiker. She abandons the corpse behind, a bit shaken but determined to make it home. Only the hitchhiker keeps chasing her for the entire ride, shouting "Thanks for the ride, lady." There is an implication that he ended up in hell and is determined to have her join him. Annie keeps trying to kill him again, only for the undead guy to keep chasing her. She does arrive home but never gets a chance to step out of the car. The hitchhiker confonts her again and her corpse is soon discovered. Cause of death: carbon monoxide poisoning.
name: Creepshow 2

deck: It is the fifth in the MGM Tarzan series to star Johnny Weissmuller and Maureen O'Sullivan.
description:
An villainous expedition team arrives on Tarzan's escarpment and kidnaps Jane and Boy in order to make Tarzan show them the location of the some gold.  
 
Soon the group is captured by natives, whereupon Tarzan comes to their rescue.
name: Tarzan's Secret Treasure

deck: Tarzan's New York Adventure is the sixth Tarzan film to feature Johnny Weissmuller and Maureen O'Sullivan. It also features an uncredited appearance of Elmo Lincoln who in 1918 was the first Tarzan.
description:
Tarzan and Jane have to go to New York to rescue Boy after he is kidnapped into a circus.   

Tarzan and Jane attempt to get Boy back first by legal means. But after this fails, Tarzan has to find an other way to rescue Boy.
name: Tarzan's New York Adventure

deck: Based on the series Higurashi no Naku Koro ni.
description: On one hot summer day in 1983, a transfer student named Maebara Keiichi comes to a peaceful rural village in Hinamizawa. There, he befriends his classmates Rena, Mion, Rika, and Satoko. Accepted as a full-fledged member of the "club," Keiichi and the gang plays all sorts of activities ranging from card and board games to hide-and-seek. But just as Keiichi was beginning to be assimilated in simple rural life, he stumbles upon the dark history of Hinamizawa. As Keiichi dives deeper into the mystery, he finds that his new found friends may not be all what they claim to be.
name: Higurashi no naku koro ni

deck: Deals with the love and friendship between two young women with contrasting personalities, yet both share the same name of Nana.
name: Nana 2

deck: Koizumi Risa an unusually tall high school girl, meets the "vertically challenged" young man Otani Atsushi. They find common ground in height anxieties and interests.
name: Love Com

deck: The trials and tribulations faced by two girls with the same name, but incredibly different personalities.
name: Nana
Higurashi no naku koro ni: Chikai

deck: A 1981 television film following the 1970s series. Marcia and Jan Brady are getting married, respectively to Wally Logan and Phillip Covington III.
name: The Brady Girls Get Married

deck: A 1988 television film following the 1970s series. Mike and Carol, retired and aging, invite all six of their children to a Christmas family reunion. But all six "children" are now adults with hectic schedules and various personal problems. Getting to the party is not as easy as it sounds.
name: A Very Brady Christmas

deck: A 1995 film featuring a new incarnation of the Bradys. They are a family with 1970s fashion sense and values living in a modern 1990s environment. Much of the humor derives from the cultural clashes resulting.
name: The Brady Bunch Movie

deck: An 1996 film following the Brady family into the 1990s. An imposter claims to be Carol's first husband, long declared missing. The Bradys are in danger of splitting up to two families, Carol's second wedding declared void.
name: A Very Brady Sequel

deck: A 2002 film for the television and video market. The President of the United States resigns while the Bradys are visiting the White House. Instead of following the presidential order of succession, Mike is selected as a "wholesome, all-American replacement".
name: The Brady Bunch in the White House

teams.name: United States Department of the Treasury

deck: Tarzan Triumphs is the seventh film with Johnny Weissmüller. Maureen O'Sullivan was unable to reprise her role as Jane due to pregnancy and the fact that the franchise had switched from MGM to RKO, and O'Sullivan was a Metro contract player.
description:
While Jane is visiting relatives in England, Zandra, white princess of a lost civilization, comes to Tarzan for help when Nazis invade the jungle and try to conquer her people and take their wealth.  
 
Tarzan, fights the Nazis after they shoot at him and captured Boy.
name: Tarzan Triumphs

deck: Tarzan's Desert Mystery is a 1943 film starring Johnny Weismüller and Nancy Kelly. It was Weissmüller's 8th Tarzan Movie and the second one produced by Sol Lesser.
description:
Jane, who is nursing British troops, asks Tarzan's help (in a letter) in obtaining a malaria serum extractable from jungle plants.  
 
Tarzan and Boy set out across the desert looking for the plants and to obtain it Tarzan must fight prehistoric monsters, Nazis... and has to team up with a American lady magician, sentenced to be hanged for carrying a secret message.
name: Tarzan's Desert Mystery

deck: This is an adventure film starring Johnny Weissmuller in his ninth outing as Tarzan. Brenda Joyce makes the first of five appearances as Jane and Johnny Sheffield returns as Boy.
description: After Boy is tricked into helping a group of explorers find an ancient city in a hidden valley of women, Tarzan must help the Queen of the Amazons in her fight against the explorers, who want to steal the city's treasures.
name: Tarzan and the Amazons

deck: Tarzan and the Leopard Woman was a 1946 action film with Johnny Weissmuller as Tarzan.
description:
After some travellers being killed, the commissioner (Dennis Hoey) asks Tarzan to look into the matter. At the same time, Tarzan, Jane, and Boy take in Kimba, a boy who claims to have become lost in the jungle. Kimba 
 
is the brother of Queen Lea, leader of a leopard cult. After the cult attacks a caravan bringing four teachers and wants to sacrifice the maidens, Tarzan has to destroy the cult and rescue Jane and Boy.
name: Tarzan and the Leopard Woman

deck: This is an adventure film starring Johnny Weissmuller in his eleventh outing as Tarzan, Brenda Joyce in her third appearance as Jane and Johnny Sheffield makes his eighth and final appearance as Boy.
description:
Due to a shortage of animals in American zoos following WW2 , Tanya Rawlins, a big-game "huntress," her financial backer and a cruel trail boss, are given permission by King Farrod, to capture a male and female of each species of animal on his land.

Oziri, nephew to King Farrod, colludes with Weir to allow him to trap more animals than bargained for, for killing King Farrod and his son, Prince Suli so he takes over the throne.

Tarzan calls all the animals from King Farrod's land across the river to his part of the jungle and systematically releases all the trapped animals from their cages. Tarzan, Boy and the surviving Prince Suli defeat both the usurping nephew and the huntress, but the latter escapes onboard a plane
name: Tarzan and the Huntress

deck: Tarzan and the Mermaids was a 1948 action film based on the Tarzan character. It was the 12th and last of the Tarzan movies to star Johnny Weissmuller in the title role.
description:
While Boy is away at school in England, a high priest is trying to force a young girl to marry an evil pearl trader posing as the god Balu.  
 
She escapes, is recaptured and is finally resued by Tarzan and Jane who reunite her with her chosen fiance.
name: Tarzan and the Mermaids

deck: Tarzan of the Apes (1918) is a silent, black and white action adventure. The movie was the first Tarzan movie ever made, and is based on Edgar Rice Burroughs' original novel Tarzan of the Apes.
description: The plot follows the novel very closely. After his parents die the newborn Tarzan is taken by a great Ape, Kala. Later the boy finds his father's knife and uses it to become King of Apes. Later Tarzan has to kill the native who killed Kala and to rescue a scientist's daughter named Jane.
name: Tarzan of the Apes

deck: This movie is a direct-to-video midquel to the 1999 Disney animated film Tarzan. It features two new songs from Phil Collins and takes place during the song "Son of Man" from the first movie.
description: The film tells the story of a young Tarzan's adventure to discover who he really is.  When Tarzan begins to see that he is not like the other gorillas, his mother Kala assures him that these slight differences only make him stronger. But when these differences put Kala in danger, he decides everyone would be better off without him and runs away....
name: Tarzan II: The Legend Begins

deck: Tarzan & Jane is a Disney direct-to-video film which continues the adventures of the characters from the 1999 animated feature Tarzan, and uses three unaired episodes of the film's corresponding television series, The Legend of Tarzan.
description: The film presents three self contained "episodes" via flashback. Jane & Tarzan's first anniversary has arrived, and Jane is trying to find a suitable present for her husband, with the help of the elephant Tantor and the gorilla Terk . When a party is suggested, they remember the disaster that occurred when three of Jane's friends arrive for a visit. As Jane considers a gift of jewellery, she is reminded of Tarzan's exploit with a pair of conniving diamond prospectors who take advantage of him and also trigger a volcanic reaction. Jane then decides on a night of dancing but changes her mind when she remembers how Bobby, one of her childhood friends, came to visit, only to be found out to be a treacherous spy to the Germans during World War I. Downhearted, Jane goes home without a present, only to find that Tarzan has put together a wonderful surprise for her.
name: Tarzan & Jane

deck: This is a Tarzan movie starring Lex Barker in his first appearance as Tarzan, while Brenda Joyce had played Jane opposite Johnny Weismuller in four previous films. Elmo Lincoln, who had been the first screen Tarzan appears uncredited as a fisherman repairing his nets.
description: An aviatrix walks out of the jungle looking decades younger than her chronological age due to a secret fountain of youth but gradually begins a terrifying accelerated aging process. Against Tarzan's wishes, she and Jane begin a desperate search for the fountain.
name: Tarzan's Magic Fountain

deck: Tarzan and the Slave Girl is a 1950 film. It is the scond one starring Lex Barker as Tarzan. Jane is played by Vanessa Brown and like many Tarzan movies, it involves a lost civilization in Africa.
description: The Lionians are a tribe dying of a mysterious disease, so their Chief decides to kidnap Jane and Lola, a half-breed nurse, in order to help repopulate his civilization. Tarzan must rescue them while fending off blowgun attacks from people called the Waddies who are disguised as bushes.
name: Tarzan and the Slave Girl

deck: Tarzan's Peril is a 1951 film starring Lex Barker as Tarzan for the third time and Virginia Huston as Jane. Some of it was shot in Kenya, making it the first Tarzan movie to be filmed in Africa.The film is frequently shown under the alternate titles Jungle Queen and Tarzan and the Jungle Queen.
description:
Radijeck, the leader of the gunrunners plans to sell two hundred guns to Bulam, a tribe leader who wants to rule the jungle and force Melmendi, a recently crowned queen of another tribe to marry him.  
 
Tarzan has to rescue Melmendi and her men and so he battles Bulam and kills him. Later Tarzan must rescue Jane, byknocking Radijeck him from Tarzan's treehouse to his death.
name: Tarzan's Peril

deck: Tarzan's Savage Fury is the fourth Tarzan film starring Lex Barker as Tarzan. This movie does make some allusions to the Tarzan novels. It notes Tarzan's relation to Britain's aristocratic Greystoke family, and the villain Rokov is clearly patterned on Rokoff, a villain in the early Tarzan novels
description:
Tarzan's cousin comes to Africa in hopes that Tarzan will help him secure a fortune in diamonds essential to England's military security.  
 
The cousin is immediately killed off by his guide Rokov who persuades an other man called Edwards to impersonate the cousin.  

Tarzan rescues a orphan boy named Joey (Boy's substitute),fights cannibals, defeats Rokov and Edwards and once more rescues Jane.
name: Tarzan's Savage Fury

deck: Tarzan and the She-Devil is is the fifth and last film starring Lex Barker as Tarzan. Joyce MacKenzie is Jane and Monique van Vooren plays the "She-Devil".
description:
Ivory poachers, headed by Lyra the She-Devil, Vargo and Fidel, capture a native tribe to carry their loot. Tarzan intervenes and is captured.  
 
Jane is also captured and believed killed, so the despairing Tarzan endures endless torture until he learns she is alive.  
 
He rises to the occasion and leads his elephants in the usual victory stampede.
name: Tarzan and the She-Devil

deck: Tarzan, the Ape Man is a 1981 adventure film directed by John Derek and starring Bo Derek as Jane. Former Tarzan actor Jock Mahoney, billed as Jack O'Mahoney, was the film's stunt coordinator. The films tagline was: "Unlike any other Tarzan you've ever seen!"
description: The movie tells the story of Tarzan & Jane from Jane's point of view. She visits her father in Africa where she joins him on an expedition. A couple of brief encounters with the Ape Man establish a (sexual) bond between her and Tarzan. When the expedition is captured by savages, Tarzan comes to the rescue them.
name: Tarzan, the Ape Man

deck: An 1923 Hungarian film featuring the vampire. Mary Land (Lene Myl) visits an insane asylum and encounters a patient claiming to be Dracula. She then experiences a series of frightening visions, uncertain if they are nightmares or reality.
description: The film is considered lost but there are surviving summaries, pictures and related information.
name: Drakula halála

deck: An 1931 adaptation of the Bram Stoker novel. Featuring Bela Lugosi in his best-known role.
name: Dracula

deck: An 1931 adaptation of the Bram Stoker novel with Carlos Villarias. This is an American Spanish-speaking film by the same company which released an English-speaking version that same year.
name: Drácula

deck: A 1936 sequel to the 1931 film(s). Scotland Yard arrests Van Helsing for the murders of Dracula and Renfield. A mysterious woman arranges for the destruction of the remains. She is Countess Marya Zaleska, Dracula's daughter and self-styled heiress.
description:
The vampiress protagonist is played by Gloria Holden. Her main opponents are Dr. Jeffrey Garth, a psychiatrist, and his love interest Janet Blake. Notably they receive wittier banter and bigger roles than their 1931 versions of Harker and Murray. The cast also includes Sandor, a moody and imposing manservant of Marya. He is intelligent, genuinely protective of her and acts as her advisor. He is in love with his lady and kills her when she rejects his advances.

Marya Zaleska was the first second generation-vampire on screen. She was also the first female vampire not depicted as subservient to a male one. She is conflicted about her vampiric status and seeks a cure for her bloodlust. However she does stalk, seduce and drain victims regularly. Her interaction with female victims reportedly features lesbianic overtones. This is a standard for the depiction of female vampires in literature since "Carmilla" (1872) by Sheridan Le Fanu but had not been seen in film before.
name: Dracula's Daughter

deck: An 1994 loose remake of "Dracula's Daughter" (1936). Dracula has just been killed by Van Helsing. Only the vampire had become addicted to the blood of drug addicts and was an easy target. Nadja, Dracula's daughter, destroys the remains but is still not free of her father's legacy.
description: Nadja is played by Elina Löwensohn . The film keeps the original's homosexual overtones. It is a black-and-white film intending to give a dream-like quality to several scenes. Flashbacks depict Nadja's childhood and Dracula's questionable parenting skills. The Wilhelmina Murray character is renamed to "Cassandra".
name: Nadja

deck: A 1943 entry in the Dracula series by Universal. The original Dracula and Marya Zaleska are dead. A son of Dracula has claimed the title, though he uses the alias "Count Alucard".
description:
The film starts with Katherine Caldwell (Louise Allbritton) heiress to a New Orleans plantation, arriving home following a vacation in Hungary. But she has changed a lot, seeming obsessed with the occult. She is soon followed by a mysterious new husband, "Alucard". Frank Stanley (Robert Paige) , her jealous boyfriend, confronts his rival with bullets. But soon discovers the new couple does not die easily.

The climax of the film has Katherine reveal she does not love Alucard. Marrying him was her way to achieve immortality through vampirism.
name: Son of Dracula

deck: A 1944  Universal film featuring a crossover of several of the protagonists in its horror series. Dr. Gustav Niemann, a "mad scientist", wants to exact revenge on the world. To do so, Gustav revives Dracula, Frankenstein's Moster and Laurence Talbot, the Wolf Man.
description: Dracula used the alias "Baron Latos".
name: House of Frankenstein

deck: An 1931 loose adaptation of the Mary Shelley novel. Several elements derive from a theatrical adaptation by Peggy Webling. Dr. Henry Frankenstein creates a monster from human parts. But its brain is defective.
description:
Major differences between the 1818 book and the film include the depictions of both major characters. The novel features Victor Frankenstein, a Swiss medical student from Geneva. He becomes obsessed with creating new life from dead parts and secretly studies alchemy. But once his creation comes to life, Victor abandons it in horror. The creature is intelligent and learns to speak, read and write by observing children being taught to do so. He then seeks vengeance against his creator for the maltreatment and neglect   with which he was treated since birth. 
 
In the film Henry Frankenstein is a member of the nobility and a doctor. He is depicted as a stereotyped "mad scientist". His creature is brutal because the brain placed in him was defective. No association between parental neglect or mistreatment and violent retaliation is made. The creature is not intelligent and appears mute except for grunts and growls.
name: Frankenstein

deck: An 1935 sequel to the 1931 film. It expands on an idea from the original novel where the monster demands a mate. Here Henry Frankenstein creates a Bride for his monster, only for the young woman to reject her suitor.
description: The monster in this film is depicted more intelligent, eloquent but desperately lonely. The Bride is played by Elsa Lanchester. Henry is joined by a sinister mentor, Dr. Septimus Pretorius. The film is considered a classic tragedy and has been both a financial and critical hit.
name: Bride of Frankenstein

deck: A insane puppet master uses animated puppets to kill people.
name: Puppet Master

deck: An 1939 entry in the Frankenstein series by Universal. Henry Frankenstein is dead. His son Wolf Frankenstein is attempting to restore his father's good name by proving the monster was not dangerous. To do so he has to revive it first.
name: Son of Frankenstein

deck: An 1942 entry in the Frankenstein series by Universal. The Monster is severely wounded and Wolf Frankenstein has abandoned it. But Ygor, his assistant, wants the Monster to live and wants his own brain placed inside it.
description: The film features Dr. Ludwig Frankenstein, son to Henry and brother to Wolf.
name: The Ghost of Frankenstein

deck: An 1943 crossover between the Frankenstein and Wolf Man series by Universal. Larry Talbot rises from his grave, discovering his werewolf curse has rendered him immortal. He goes seeking a way to die in the secrets of the Frankenstein family.
name: Frankenstein Meets the Wolf Man

deck: An 1941 horror film. Larry Talbot returns to his ancestral home in Wales to reconcile with his father. Trying to save a girl from a wolf, he is bitten. Larry soon finds himself the newest werewolf in the area.
name: The Wolf Man

deck: An 1945 sequel to the "House of Frankenstein". Dracula and Wolf Man seek cures to their respective curses. But their blood lust is still strong.
name: House of Dracula

deck: A 1948 horror comedy by Universal. Chick Young (Bud Abbott) and Wilbur Grey (Lou Costello) are employed by a House of Horrors museum whose latest acquisitions are the remains of Dracula and Frankenstein's monster. But the undead duo are soon revived.
description: Wolf Man appears, having trailed his enemies all the way from Europe. The Invisible Man has a cameo at the finale. The film was a swan song for the Dracula, Frankenstein and Wolf Man series by Universal. The Studio would not reuse any of the characters for decades.
name: Abbott and Costello Meet Frankenstein

deck: Baba Yaga, a mysterious and seductive witch casts a spell over fashion photographer Valentina
name: Baba Yaga

name: Tex e il Signore degli Abissi

name: Sturmtruppen

deck: Originally a book written by Neil Gaiman. The story of a girl who was bored with life and discovered a alternate world hidden behind the wall of her living room. The world is everything she ever wanted but all is not what it seems.
description: The original book has illustrations by famous artist Dave McKean.
name: Coraline

name: Puppet Master III: Toulon's Revenge

deck: In the underworld, the demon lord Sutekh has created a pack of diminutive servants called Totems to hunt and kill anyone close to bringing back the dead.
name: Puppet Master 4

deck: Continuing from the previous film the demon lord Sutekh continues his hunt for the Puppets.
name: Puppet Master 5: The Final Chapter

deck: The sixth sequel to the Puppet Master series.
name: Curse of the Puppet Master

deck: In Japanese Kôkaku kidôtai, one of the most impressive adult anime films, ever.
name: Ghost in the Shell

deck: An 1953 Turkish film. It is based on the novel "Impaler Voivode" (1928) by Ali Riza Seyfi, which is a remake of Bram Stoker's original work. The vampire moves to Istanbul and sets his eyes on Güzin (Annie Ball), an exotic dancer. Drakula Istanbul'da is the third Dracula picturization worldwide.
description: Interestingly the general appearance of this Dracula seems to be based on Count Orlock while his costume follows that of the Bela Lugosi's Dracula. The film moves the action to a modern setting and is more explicit in depiction of death scenes and sexuality.
name: Drakula Istanbulda

deck: An 1958 American film with the title character played by Francis Lederer. In the small town of Carleton, California the Mayberry family expect their Czech cousin, artist Bellac Gordal. Only Gordal is dead and the imposter using his name is Dracula.
description:
Dracula attempts to seduce his "cousin" Rachel Mayberry (Norma Eberhardt).

Dracula also seduces and vampirizes Jennie Blake (Victoria Vincent), a blind girl.
name: The Return of Dracula

deck: The first film of the Dracula series by Hammer films, featuring Christopher Lee. Dracula is targeted for assassination by Jonathan Harker, vampire hunter but quickly turns the tables on him. He now retaliates against Van Helsing, Harker's mentor.
description:
The film places Castle Dracula in the vicinity of Klausenburg/Cluj Napoca, the historical capital of Transylvania and fourth largest city in Romania. Dracula seems to travel to Germany to face Van Helsing and the Holmwood family. Despite this being a British film, no part of the action takes place on Great Britain.

This is the first film to both feature Harker as a vampire and dispose of him within minutes of its start. Arthur Holmwood is cast as brother to Lucy and husband to Mina. Dr. John Seward is given a cameo and Quincey Morris omitted.
name: Horror of Dracula

deck: An 1960 entry in the Dracula series by Hammer. Dracula himself does not appear at all. Baron Meinster (David Peele), a disciple of Dracula, follows in his mentor's footsteps. Van Helsing has to face the junior vampire and the women Meinster vampirized.
description: Meinster initially targets Marianne Danielle (Yvonne Monlaur), a young schoolteacher. But following her leads the vampire to an all-girls' school. He soon starts recruiting several young "Brides". Van Helsing h
name: Brides of Dracula

deck: The second movie based on the Italian comic strip "Sturmtruppen"
name: Sturmtruppen 2 - Tutti al fronte

deck: An 1966 entry in the Dracula series by Hammer. Klove (Philip Latham), a loyal servant of Dracula, has been guarding Castle Dracula for a decade following the demise of his Lord. When unexpected visitors arrive, Klove uses a blood ritual to resurrect his master.
description:
The two female leads are sister-in-laws Helen Kent (Barbara Shelley) and Diana Kent (Suzan Farmer). The ritual bringing Dracula back to life involves a victim's throat slit directly above Dracula's remains and the blood dropping on them.

The resurrected Dracula never speaks but stalks victims and attacks in silence, even gaining entry in a monastery to do so. This is considered to have added to the sense of menace from him and ended up making the film "creerpier". Actually there were several lines written for Dracula in the script. Christopher Lee, the actor depicting him, thought the dialogue was extremely poor and refused to utter any of its lines.

The finale does not have Dracula killed. He is left trapped beneath icy waters.
name: Dracula: Prince of Darkness

deck: The movie with the british character Jane.
name: Jane and the Lost City

deck: An 1968 entry in the Dracula series by Hammer. Dracula's habit of throwing the corpses of his latest victims in a church has caused the population around his castle to lose faith. A Monsignor of the Roman Catholic Church decides to retaliate against the vampire.
description:
The film takes place c. 1905. The main opponents of Dracula are Monsignor Ernest Muller (Rupert Davies), depicted as a holy man, and Paul (Barry Andrews), boyfriend of Muller's niece. Said niece is Anna Muller (Marion Mathie) who is Dracula's prey of choice. Dracula's servant is a nameless Priest (Ewan Hooper) who lost his faith due to Dracula's actions.

Dracula is motivated by revenge because Muller has placed a large metal cross at the gate of Castle Dracula. Leaving Dracula unable to enter and effectively homeless. Paul is a self-declared atheist, though his dialogue points to him being agnostic instead. Paul manages to stake Dracula early in their encounter but his lack of faith allows Dracula to escape death. The Priest has to regain his faith in order to help finish the job.
name: Dracula Has Risen from the Grave

deck: An 1970 entry in the Dracula series by Hammer. An English traveler witnesses the death scene of Dracula from the previous film. He collects the dried-up blood, cloak and ring og the vampire. But these remains ensure Dracula will return.
description:
The traveler sells them to Lord Courtley (Ralph Bates), a dispossesed nobleman and would-be black sorcerer. Courtley has offered his services to three wealthy, middle-aged but bored gentlemen who were looking for new thrills in life. The magic ritual Courtley attempts has him drinking Dracula's blood.His body is taken over by Dracula and the only effect of the ritual has been to bring the Vampire Lord back to life.

Dracula is eager to provide new thrills for the trio of gentlemen, by turning first their daughters and then their sons to minions. Then using the children to assassinate the parents. Memorably a scene has two of the girls killing one of the three gentlemen by putting a stake through his heart, a reverse of the typical situation with vampires.
name: Taste the Blood of Dracula

deck: An 1970 entry in the Dracula series by Hammer. The villagers around Castle Dracula have had enough. The men storm Castle Dracula while the women hide within the village church. But all women are later found slain within said church.
description:
The faces of the female corpses are left scarred, ripped to pieces by a vampire bat. A new pet for Dracula, the bat appears through the film whenever Dracula wants to access an otherwise protected location. They both appear together so this is not simply Dracula shape-shifting. Left unmentioned is that vampire bats, all three species, are indigenous to the Americas.

The film depicts Dracula as far crueler than previously seen. Drinking blood seems to be a secondary concern. He seems more interested in torturing victims, whipping them to exhaustion, burning them alive, impaling them. The later practice brings his demise. Dracula actually wins his final fight against main opponent Simon Carlson (Dennis Waterman). He is preparing to impale Carlton on a metal instrument, when a lightnig bolt strikes said instrument. dracula is electrocuted to death. For once the raging storm around the climactic battle was not part of the scenery.
name: Scars of Dracula

deck: An 1972 entry in the Dracula series by Hammer. The film abandons the Victorian(1837 - 1901) and Edwardian (1901 - 1910) setting of previous films. Dracula has survived to the 1970s and is now active in modern London.
description:
A hundred years have passed since Dracula and Lawrence Van Helsing killed each other in their final battle. Johnny Alucard, a descendant of Dracula's servants, manages to bring the Vampire Lord back to life. Dracula goes after the descendants of the Van Helsing family: Lorrimer Van Helsing and his young granddaughter Jessica (Stephanie Beacham).

Dracula is interested in Jessica in more ways than one, while also preying on her friends. He plans to turn her into a vampire as his final revenge to the Van Helsing family. Lorrimer is forced to follow the family tradition in vampire hunting.
name: Dracula A.D. 1972

deck: An 1973 entry in the Dracula series by Hammer. Dracula poses as D. D. Denham, a reclusive property developer. He has formed a cult which includes prominent members of British society.
description:
Dracula's followers include both humans and vampires in this film. The cult is investigated by both Scotland Yard and MI6, but members retaliate by abducting employees of either service. The authorities turn to the expert, Lorrimer Van Helsing.

Dracula's titular plan is to release a new strain of the Bubonic plague on humanity and then cease power amids the chaoes. He wants Jessica Van Helsing to be his consort. Lorrimer notes Dracula's plan is more likely to wipe out humanity and starve vampires to death. He speculates Dracula has tired of his existence and harbors a death wish. But he wants everyone to die with him.
name: Satanic Rites of Dracula
